                    <head type="section" tid="1">Identity</head>
                    <milestone unit="chunk" xml:id="EFT-KB-YAMARI-1"/>
                    <p tid="2">The name "Jamāri" (dza mā ri) is given as author/translator in the colophons of three Tengyur texts. In the Sanskrit text for Toh. 4226 the author's name is given as
                        "Yamāri". "Jamāri" would appear to be the Prakṛt/Apabhraṃśa form of his name, given the attestation in a Sanskrit manuscript. </p>
